Remote Code Execution Vulnerability Disclosed in Windows JScript Component
Recent flaws discovered in handling of error objects by JScript, allows attacker to execute arbitrary code. Although exploitation does not lead to a full system compromise.
https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/remote-code-execution-vulnerability-disclosed-in-windows-jscript-component/

Banking Botnet Operators Team Up to Leverage IcedID and TrickBot Trojan
Researchers discovered the collaboration while studying the IcedID malware – they quickly realized that computers infected with IcedID were also downloading the other Trojan, TrickBot.
https://threatpost.com/botnet-operators-team-up-to-leverage-icedid-trickbot-trojans/132392/

Q4 DDoS report 2017: From bad to worse
According to the Q4 2017 Global DDoS Threat Landscape Report the number of application layer attacks nearly doubled, just as the number of network layer assaults declined. In both cases, however, attacks grew more persistent.
http://www.information-age.com/ddos-report-2017-123472141/

